==== INSTALLATION ====


======== KNOWN ISSUES ========

---- assumed array shapes ----
assumed array shapes are not supported in C or Python and compiler dependent. The file 
PythonWrapper.f95 provides wrapper subroutines that converts arrays from assumed to
explicit shapes.

---- optional return parameters ----
optional return parameters are not supported in C or Python. We either have
to return them always which is memory intensive and not good for speed, or
we need two separate subroutines. Affected routines:

======== WRAPPED AND UNWRAPPED FUNCTIONS ========

= LEGENDRE FUNCTIONS =

ALL WRAPPED

= SPHERICAL HARMONIC TRANSFORMATIONS =

-- wrapped: --
MakeGridDH
SHExpandDH
MakeGridDHC
SHExpandDHC
MakeGridGLQ
SHExpandGLQ
MakeGridGLQC
SHExpandGLQC
PreCompute (partially - optional parameters)
SHRead     (partially - optional parameters)

-- unwrapped: --
DHaj
GLQGridCoord
PreGLQ
NGLQ
NGLQSH
NGLQSHN
SHExpandLSQ
MakeGrid2D
MakeGridPoint
SHMultiply

= GLOBAL SPECTRAL ANALYSIS =

-- wrapped: --
SHPowerSpectrum
SHPowerSpectrumDensity

= IO/STORAGE/ =

-- wrapped: --
SHrtoc (bug in SHrtoc fortran function: case convention=1 does nothing)
SHctor (bug in SHctor fortran function: case convention=1 does nothing)
